narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This isn't the most intensive writing workshop in the world, but it is a great excuse to read good nonfiction and to improve your own writing by example. Class discussions are really fun if you have a mixed group of people who disagree a lot. The course is worth suffering through the motherload of Hazlitt on the syllabus.
YES-great class to learn how to write.
This is a great class. A smart, interesting mix of students. Bromwich is not only brilliant, but also warm and helpful. A cool blend of outside reading and workshopping for a writing seminar.
I would recommend this class to a student who is already confident enough in their writing to not be too encouraged or too deterred by any of Prof. Bromwich's rather cutting insights.
You'll do a bit of reading, Hazlitt, Orwell, Woolf,and writing about cool stuff, a mini biography, an art review, etc.Yes take it. Bromwich is BRILLIANT. Take it for that reason only.
If you are interested in writing and reading the great writers, this is a class for you.
